@posita In the case you want to reuse an existing router:

``` python
class BaseApi(object):
    router = Klein()

    @router.route('/')
    def index(self, request):
         return "foo"

class ChildApi(BaseApi):
    router = copy.copy(BaseApi.router)

    @router.route('/bar')
    def bar(self, request):
        return 'bar'

class OtherChildApi(BaseApi):
    router = copy.copy(BaseApi.router)
    
    @router.route('/bar')
    def other_bar(self, request):
        return "This is other bar"
```

