@glennhickey So every time the pipeline makes calls to Docker, it expects the directory /data to exist in each Docker container the pipeline make a call to. In docker, if the directory of the container doesn't exist then Docker automatically creates it in the container (http://stackoverflow.com/a/24641998). Apparently singularities `--bind` option doesn't do that with their images.

I've been getting the following types of errors when making singularity calls. The containers should all contain a /data directory as per the specification defined by @hannes-ucsc @jvivian @cket in the old cgl-docker-lib repo (https://github.com/BD2KGenomics/cgl-docker-lib#basic-philosophy).

To maintain consistancy, the main vg Dockerfile should include the creation of a `/data` directory as illustrated here (https://github.com/BD2KGenomics/cgl-docker-lib/blob/master/vg/runtime/Dockerfile).

