@ardunn, The reason I have `integrate.quad` in the code is so that a user can use any function that they want as the bin. For that reason, I wouldn't want to put in the analytical solution for the integral. Rewriting the sorting function without lambdas is possible, but not allowing arbitrary functions for the bins defeats the generality of this featurizer.

